relevant_findings.general: No acute distress. Oriented to person, place, and time. Mood and affect appropriate.
relevant_findings.HEENT: Normocephalic, atraumatic. Sclera anicteric, pupils equal, round, reactive to light, extraocular movements intact. Conjunctivae pink, no pallor or cyanosis of oral mucosa. No xanthalesma.
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: PMI located in the midclavicular line, normal S1 and S2, semilunar murmur increased with Valsalva maneuver. No thrills, lifts. No S3 or S4.
relevant_findings.respiratory: No chest wall deformities, breathing unlabored, no accessory muscle use, clear to auscultation bilaterally, no crackles, wheezes, or rhonchi.
relevant_findings.abdomen: Soft abdomen with tenderness in LLQ and LUQ, no pain at rest, no rebound or guarding. No hepatosplenomegaly.
relevant_findings.extremities: No clubbing, cyanosis, or edema. No femoral bruits.
relevant_findings.skin: No stasis dermatitis, ulcers, scars, or xanthomas.
